	<text>
		<body>
			<pb n="1"/>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>New Orleans</placeName> <date>Jany 9<hi rend="sup">th</hi> 1846</date></p>
				<p><add>Hebrew</add></p>
				<p>Revd Sir&#44;I trust that the purport of my letter will<lb/> be a sufficient excuse for thus intruding on your valuable time.<lb/>  You are aware that I am the Secretary of the Congregation<lb/> &#8220;Shanarai Chased&#8221;&#44; which congregation I have but lately<lb/> joined&#59; I did so thinking that I might perhaps be of service<lb/> to them&#44; after the division made&#44; by the fen&#45;Portuguese Members.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">A case of peculiar interest is now before the Congregations and<lb/> I wish your opinion and instructions on the subject.  It is as follows.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">A gentleman&#8212;a very old and long inhabitant of this City&#44;<lb/> &#40;<persName>Mr Alexander Phillips</persName>&#41; married according to Christian <hi rend="underline">rites</hi>&#44;<lb/> a Christian woman&#59; he has a large family by this <hi rend="underline">Christian</hi><lb/> wife&#59; his sons have not been made Hebrews&#59; neither has his<lb/> sons or daughters been christened or baptized&#59; and I do believe<lb/> that they have all been brought up to believe themselves Jews &#38; Jewesses.<lb/>  A daughter of this <sic>gentlemen</sic> and Christian woman has lately<lb/> been engaged to be married to an Israelite &#40;<persName>Mr Haber</persName>&#41; and the<lb/> parties wish the marriage to be solemnized in this Congregation&#44;<lb/> I am of the opinion&#44; and have so stated&#44; that the girl must go<lb/> through the regular and complete forms&#44; requisite to make a<lb/> <add>Hebrew</add>&#44; and such was the unanimous opinion of most of the Israelites<lb/> in this place.  I am sorry to say that I think money has induced<lb/> these people to alter their opinion&#59; they have also told me that a</p>
			<pb n="2"/>
				<p>a person whom they say is <add>Hebrew</add> in <placeName>Baltimore</placeName>&#44; has decided&#44;<lb/> that as the lady is of an Hebrew father&#44; and&#44; in consideration<lb/> that she has never been baptized &#38;c&#59; it is not necessary for her to<lb/> go through the forms to make her a <add>Hebrew</add>.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Not knowing the<lb/> gentleman of <placeName>Baltimore</placeName>&#44; I respectfully beg of you to give me<lb/> the particulars &#40;plain&#41; of what has to be done.  For this is<lb/> a matter in which all <placeName>Israel</placeName> is concerned&#59; for if we do<lb/> not keep a sharp look out&#44; we will become so intermixed<lb/> with strangers&#44; that it must cause great confusion in our ranks</p>
			<p rend="indent(9)">I am Reverend Sir</p>
			<p rend="indent(9)">Yours Respectfully</p>
			<p rend="indent(9)"><persName role="author">Benjamin W&#58; Cohen</persName></p>
				<p><addressee>Revd I&#58; Leeser</addressee>.</p>
			<pb n="4"/>
				<p><addressee>Revd I&#58; Leeser</addressee>.</p>
